caption: One of the most stunning synagogues I saw in my life. The organised tour (10 Euros per person) reveales very interesting stories and photos. Very recommended.

What a beautiful synagogue with so much history.  I went there on Thursday at around 15:00, and together with a couple from the US we were given a very thorough tour of the synagogue.  Such a wonderful experience that I can definitely recommend.
Impressive building and very excitement visit inside. We had great ceremony for Shabbat pray and great hospitality for dinner. Highly recommended.
Beautiful synagogue. Interesting history. If you're lucky enough to go while there is a service, the acoustics in the sanctuary are phenomenal.

Great majestic synagogue! They can improve on the Shabbat service! They never brought the torah by the ladies section. The Kudosh cookies(6 boxes!!); the way they were presented in their own boxes do not match this grand place! Better off with only the wine blessing. Spending the least €500/week for flowers and food catering would do this place some justice! Should have a women club to take care of this!
A place with an amazing history. The exterior and interior design is charming.

Beautiful synagogue really big and very kind community. However the back building including the toilets is in terrible conditions which is disgraceful considering you need to wash your hands for prayers.

What a beautiful Shul, one of the biggest in Europe. Ask for Victor when visiting, he's amazing and knows history of Shul well. Attend  Kidush lunch, everyone is great!

We entered the door of the Great Synagogue of Paris and we were welcomed with great kindness and kindness. A quick visit and a few anecdotes later, we are amazed with an invitation to come for a Saturday morning Shabbat. THANKS !
Built under Napoleon III, it is the main synagogue of the Jewish community of Paris. A place to visit to understand and discover Judaism.

The Great Synagogue of Paris, located rue de la Victoire, is an architectural and spiritual jewel in the heart of the French capital. Its impressive facade and beautifully ornate interior reflect the richness of Jewish tradition. I have had the privilege of attending church services and community events at this iconic venue, and each visit has been a deeply inspiring experience. The atmosphere of contemplation and spiritual connection that reigns in this synagogue is simply remarkable. Whether for a religious celebration, a cultural visit or simply to discover its fascinating history, I highly recommend discovering the Great Synagogue of Paris.

One could pass by without noticing this monument. The interior courtyard is a haven of peace. The interior of the synagogue is impressive, gold and purple. So many, decorated seats, the light from the stained glass windows. A guided tour is essential to fully appreciate the visit.
I just called the Synagogue to ask a question and was very warmly received. A great joy to feel such kindness. 🤗🙏🏻❤ …
